description:
&lt;p&gt;Prisons are one of the most challenging, yet rewarding places for healthcare professionals to work - if you’re looking for a role where you can develop your existing skills and learn something new every day, then this may be the role for you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lancashire and South Cumbria Operational Delivery Network for the elimination of Hepatitis C recognise the fact that prisoners are a socially excluded group with complex healthcare needs that can often be associated with poor outcomes. We believe that putting the patient first, regardless of the environment or their history, we can achieve elimination of Hepatitis C ahead of the WHO target of 2030.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting fixed term / secondment opportunity of 18 months for a talented Senior support worker to assist in establishing the hep c service within our local prisons. Substantial experience ( minimum 3 years) at band 3 in a related setting or prison is essential for this role. You should ideally be qualified at NVQ level 3 in a health related subject .We are looking a senior support worker with a real passion for developing clinical skills and pathways in an environment that is ever changing. You must be self-motivated and able to work autonomously as well as showing plenty of initiative when it comes to working in a wide range of situations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some agile working is feasible due to a mix of base between the prisons, community , hospital and home . Office accommodation has been secured at AVH however this will be allocated om a weekly rota.Please see Agile Working Policy attached.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have a flexible approach working within a team that encourages new ideas and opinions on how to improve the service.&lt;br /&gt;The role is specific to hepatitis C management within a prison setting and also as part of the wider Hepatology teams making a key contribution to the elimination of hepatitis C . You will assist the Registered Nurses in establish outreach services within the prisons including telemedicine and assist in developing a regional case finding programme by linking prison based services with the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Lancashire and South Cumbria ODN will offer training and development within our friendly and supportive multidisciplinary team to develop this role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also involve some administrative and clerical duties related directly to hepatitis C including the collecting and recording of data on an electronic databases and candidates should be familiar with the use of Microsoft Office, particularly Excel spread sheets&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Car owner / driver is essential&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jane Grassham – Project Manager – jane.grassham@elht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ioannis Gkikas – Clinical lead – Ioannis.gkikas@elht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
